---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="What is a battery?" description="Learn how batteries work using chemistry — oxidation, reduction and electron flow explained">
  <style>
    .article-header { background: #3C3489; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .tags { display: flex; gap: 8px; margin-bottom: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .tag { font-size: 11px; padding: 3px 10px; border-radius: 999px; font-weight: 500; }
    .article-title { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 600; color: #EEEDFE; line-height: 1.3; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .objective { background: #534AB7; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; font-size: 14px; color: #EEEDFE; }
    .objective strong { color: #FAC775; }
    .vocab-box { background: #EEEDFE; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .vocab-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #3C3489; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .vocab-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 10px; }
    .vocab-item { background: white; border-radius: 8px; padding: 0.75rem 1rem; }
    .vocab-word { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; color: #3C3489; margin-bottom: 3px; }
    .vocab-def { font-size: 13px; color: #555; line-height: 1.5; }
    .video-link { display: block; background: #1a1a2e; border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; text-decoration: none; text-align: center; }
    .video-icon { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 8px; }
    .video-title { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #EEEDFE; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .video-subtitle { font-size: 13px; color: #AFA9EC; }
    .facts-box { background: #f5f5f5; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .facts-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #3C3489; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 12px; }
    .fact { display: flex; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; align-items: flex-start; }
    .fact-dot { width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%; background: #3C3489; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 6px; }
    .fact-text { font-size: 15px; color: #1a1a2e; line-height: 1.6; }
    .fact-text strong { color: #3C3489; }
    .summary-box { background: #3C3489; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
    .summary-title { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #FAC775; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 10px; }
    .summary-text { font-size: 15px; color: #EEEDFE; line-height: 1.7; }
    .topic-tags { display: flex; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 2rem; }
    .topic-tag { font-size: 12px; padding: 5px 12px; border-radius: 999px; }
  </style>

  <div class="article-header">
    <div class="tags">
      <span class="tag" style="background:#EEEDFE;color:#3C3489;">General</span>
      <span class="tag" style="background:#EEEDFE;color:#3C3489;">Electrochemistry</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="article-title">What is a battery?</h1>
    <div class="objective"><strong>Learning objective:</strong> Explain how a battery works using the principles of oxidation, reduction and electron flow.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="vocab-box">
    <div class="vocab-title">Key vocabulary</div>
    <div class="vocab-grid">
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Oxidation</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">The loss of electrons. A substance that loses electrons is oxidized.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Reduction</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">The gain of electrons. A substance that gains electrons is reduced.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Redox reaction</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A reaction where oxidation and reduction happen at the same time. One substance loses electrons while another gains them.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Electrode</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">A conductor through which electricity enters or leaves a substance. Batteries have two electrodes — anode and cathode.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Anode</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">The negative electrode. Oxidation happens here — electrons are released.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="vocab-item">
        <div class="vocab-word">Cathode</div>
        <div class="vocab-def">The positive electrode. Reduction happens here — electrons are absorbed.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=how+does+a+battery+work+chemistry+high+school" target="_blank" class="video-link">
    <div class="video-icon">▶</div>
    <div class="video-title">Watch on YouTube</div>
    <div class="video-subtitle">Search: how does a battery work chemistry high school</div>
  </a>

  <div class="facts-box">
    <div class="facts-title">Key facts</div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">A battery converts <strong>chemical energy into electrical energy</strong> through a redox reaction. Electrons flow from one electrode to the other through an external circuit.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">Every battery has two electrodes — the <strong>anode</strong> (negative) where oxidation occurs and the <strong>cathode</strong> (positive) where reduction occurs.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text"><strong>OIL RIG</strong> is a useful memory tool — Oxidation Is Loss, Reduction Is Gain. In a battery the anode loses electrons (oxidation) and the cathode gains electrons (reduction).</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">A simple battery can be made from <strong>two different metals</strong> in an electrolyte solution. The more reactive metal acts as the anode and releases electrons to the less reactive metal.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
      <div class="fact-dot"></div>
      <div class="fact-text">Modern <strong>lithium-ion batteries</strong> in phones and laptops work on the same principle — lithium ions move between electrodes during charging and discharging.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="summary-box">
    <div class="summary-title">Summary</div>
    <div class="summary-text">
      A battery works by using a redox reaction to convert chemical energy into electrical energy. At the anode oxidation occurs and electrons are released, while at the cathode reduction occurs and electrons are absorbed. The flow of electrons from anode to cathode through an external circuit is what we call electric current.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-tags">
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#EEEDFE;color:#3C3489;">Electrochemistry</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#FAEEDA;color:#633806;">General</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#FAECE7;color:#712B13;">Redox</span>
    <span class="topic-tag" style="background:#E6F1FB;color:#0C447C;">Oxidation</span>
  </div>
</Layout>
